    <div>
        <p><b>16. <i>CERTIFICATION REGARDING POLITICAL CONTRIBUTIONS, FEES, AND COMMISSIONS (<a href='http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22'> ITAR PART 130</a>)</i></b></p>

        <p> Please note 22 CFR &sect; 130.12(b) requires Supplier to respond to this section <b><u>within 20 days</u></b>, unless Supplier provides the information directly to the U.S. State Department in accordance with 22 CFR &sect; 130.12(c).  U.S. law requires Honeywell to inform the Department of State if we have not received a response within 25 days of this request.  Additionally, 22 CFR &sect; 130.14 requires Supplier to maintain the records upon which the information below is based for a minimum of five (5) years from the date of the report. </p>

        <p>A. <i>SUPPLIER</i> certifies it <b>SELLS</b> defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Honeywell that are:  (1) controlled for export under U.S. International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) (22 CFR Parts 120-130); <b>and</b> (2) valued in an amount of $500,000 or more (sold $500,000 or more in ITAR controlled goods to Honeywell); <b>and</b> (3) for delivery (or incorporation into another product for delivery) to, or for the use of, the armed forces of an international organization or a country other than the United States. </p>

        <p style="margin-left:20px">
